net.bytebuddy.dynamic

Interface DynamicType.Builder.MatchedMethodInterception<S>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - The most specific known loaded type that is implemented by the created dynamic type, usually the type itself, an interface or the direct super class.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DynamicType.Builder.ExceptionDeclarableMethodInterception<S>, DynamicType.Builder.OptionalMatchedMethodInterception<S>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DynamicType.Builder.AbstractBase.DefaultExceptionDeclarableMethodInterception, DynamicType.Builder.AbstractBase.DefaultMatchedMethodInterception, DynamicType.Builder.AbstractBase.DefaultOptionalMatchedMethodInterception
    Enclosing interface:
    DynamicType.Builder<T>

    public static interface DynamicType.Builder.MatchedMethodInterception<S>
    Defines an implementation for a method that was added to this instrumentation or a to method selection of existing methods.

    • Method Detail

      • intercept

        DynamicType.Builder.MethodAnnotationTarget<S> intercept(Implementation implementation)
        Intercepts the currently selected methods with the provided implementation. If this intercepted method is not yet declared by the current type, it might be added to the currently built type as a result of this interception. If the method is already declared by the current type, its byte code code might be copied into the body of a synthetic method in order to preserve the original code's invokeability.
        Parameters:
        implementation - The implementation to apply to the currently selected method.
        Returns:
        A builder which will intercept the currently selected methods by the given implementation.

      • intercept

                                                        ModifierResolver modifierResolver)
        Intercepts the currently selected method by a given implementation.
        Parameters:

        modifierResolver - The modifier resolver to apply to the instrumented method.
        Returns:

      • withDefaultValue

        DynamicType.Builder.MethodAnnotationTarget<S> withDefaultValue(Object value)
        Defines a default annotation value to set for any matched method. The value is to be represented in a wrapper format, enum values should be handed as EnumerationDescription instances, annotations as AnnotationDescription instances and Class values as TypeDescription instances. Other values are handed in their actual form or as their wrapper types.
        Parameters:
        value - A non-loaded value that the annotation property should set as a default.
        Returns:
        A builder which defines the given default value for all matched methods.

      • withDefaultValue

        DynamicType.Builder.MethodAnnotationTarget<S> withDefaultValue(Object value,
                                                               ModifierResolver modifierResolver)
        Defines a default annotation value to set for any matched method. The value is to be represented in a wrapper format, enum values should be handed as EnumerationDescription instances, annotations as AnnotationDescription instances and Class values as TypeDescription instances. Other values are handed in their raw format or as their wrapper types.
        Parameters:
        value - A non-loaded value that the annotation property should set as a default.
        modifierResolver - The modifier resolver to apply to the instrumented method.
        Returns:
        A builder which defines the given default value for all matched methods.
